This paper deals with privacy-preserving data analysis on streams, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the problem of estimating predicate sums for sliding windows and other decay models, which involves data structures and algorithms for processing data streams (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the accuracy and error bounds of the proposed algorithms, which is related to the field of databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper uses concepts from information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the privacy guarantees of the proposed algorithms.
